English club, Bristol City, on Saturday, sacked their manager, Lee Johnson, following their 1-0 home defeat against Cardiff City in the Championship today. Bristol City made this known in a statement via thier official website. “Lee Johnson was this evening relieved of his role as Bristol City Head Coach,” a club statement read. “Current Assistant Head Coach Dean Holden will take over immediately in a caretaker capacity as the club looks to appoint a successor.” Bristol are currently occupying the 12th position on the Championship table with 55 points from 41 matches.